Warning: don't use -server or bitcoind where you web browse (v0.3.2 and
lower)

Bitcointalk

2010-07-19 16:01:38 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Donʼt use the -server or -daemon switch or run bitcoind on a machine
   where you use a web browser.  It opens port 8332 on 127.0.0.1, the
   local loopback address, and you wouldnʼt think that web browsers could
   cross-site access it, but it is possible.
   Weʼre working on a release soon that puts a password on the JSON-RPC
   interface, but until then, avoid using the -server switch, and donʼt
   web browse on the same machine where bitcoind is running.
   Update:
   The JSON-RPC HTTP authentication feature in 0.3.3 solves this problem.
